05/Mar/19 1:18 AM;bstasyszyn;[~denniskuhnert] The main problem is that the SDK doesn't know whether the 'access denied' error is transient (as in the case of the peer being pruned) or fatal (as in the case of the user being revoked). So I think the decision on what to do in the case of an error should be made by the client (i.e. the user of the SDK). I propose the following:
 - Add a WithErrorHandler(handler) option to the SDK which would allow the client to be notified of errors
 - Add a CloseContext(ctxt) function to the SDK which would shut down all resources associated with a given client context

For example:
{code:java}
errHandler := func(ctxt fab.ClientContext, channelID string, err error) {
  if err.Error() == "access denied" {
    sdk.CloseContext(ctxt)
    // Need to recreate channel/resmgmt clients that were using this context
  } else {
    // Probably just a transient error - do nothing
  }
}{code}
